The goal is to maximize a concave function of time average utilities subject to equilibrium constraints. The paper proposes a Lyapunov method to solve the problem in an online max-weight fashion. Hence, it is highly likely that this paper belongs to the Game Theory sub-category.
2. cs.LG (Machine Learning): The paper proposes a method to solve a repeated stochastic game. The algorithm does not require knowledge of the event probabilities and has polynomial convergence time. Hence, it is possible that this paper belongs to the Machine Learning sub-category.
3. cs.SY (Systems and Control): The paper proposes a Lyapunov method to solve a repeated stochastic game. The method is based on selecting actions based on a set of time-varying weights. Hence, it is possible that this paper belongs to the Systems and Control sub-category.
4. cs.IT (Information Theory): The paper deals with a time-varying game with multiple players and a common source of randomness.
